  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "Network Engineer / Administrator",
  "description": "<p>Our Client, a Prestigious leading firm is seeking to recruit a Network Engineer/Administrator for the IT department.<br /><br /><strong>Location: </strong>Central Singapore<br /></p><p><strong>Responsibilities:</strong></p><ul><li>Oversee daily network operations (on-premises and cloud) for Singapore’s office and its regional office in Asia. Ensure network security, compliance, and business continuity. Report to\nInfrastructure Manager.</li><li>Manage network projects (planning, design, implementation)</li><li>Troubleshoot network issues (routers, switches, wireless, load balancers)</li><li>Monitor and optimize network performance</li><li>Ensure network security and compliance</li><li>Collaborate with teams on network security policies and procedures</li><li>Perform daily health checks and capacity planning</li><li>Manage and maintain Data Center facilities, cleanliness and security</li><li>Liaise with vendors and network carriers to ensure services are met according to the Service Level Agreement</li><li>Provide 24/7 level 2 support relating to all network issues</li></ul><p><strong>Requirements:</strong></p><ul><li>Degree or Diploma in IT/Computer Engineering/Computer Science or any related field of\nstudies</li><li>Possess 2 to 4 years of related Network experience </li><li>Candidates must be familiar with L2/L3 experience in network and multi-cloud</li><li>CCNA/CCNP or equivalent certification is of an added advantage but non-essential</li><li>Possess<strong> </strong>ITIL knowledge, including but not limited to service and Change management</li><li>Good communication skills</li><li>Self-motivated team player</li></ul>",
